5 8. libyphoenices. The Phoenician settlers who had many centuries before settled in the interior of Africa, were supposed to have come through Sidon, and to be agricultural tribes dispossessed perhaps by J oshua from Palestine. As such they betook themselves not to trade but husbandry in their new homes, and by their mixture with the natives gave rise to a new race, whose name implies this fusion, like the Celtiberi, or the mixed race in the South of Spain, where the Carthagi- nians continued the system oi colonies near the coast.
